Class OfflineStorageManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xamoom.android.xamoomsdk.Storage.OfflineStorageManager

  • public class OfflineStorageManager
extends java.lang.Object
    OfflineStorageManager is used to communicate with the databaseAdapters to save, query and delete data.

      • saveContent

        public boolean saveContent(Content content,
                           boolean queueDownload,
                           DownloadManager.OnDownloadManagerCompleted completion)
                    throws java.net.MalformedURLException
        Saves content object and it's contentBlocks. Will automatically save content image and media files from contentblocks (images, videos, audio).
        Parameters:
        content - Content object to save.
        queueDownload - True to queue download. Use DownloadManager.downloadQueriedTasks() to start download.
        completion - DownloadCompletion. @return true if successfully saved to database.
        Throws:
        java.net.MalformedURLException - if file url is badly formatted.

                          boolean saveDeletion)
                   throws java.io.IOException
        Delete file from phone storage.
        Parameters:
        url - Url of the file.
        saveDeletion - True to save and delete a patch with check if the file is somewhere else.
        Returns:
        true when deleted. False when not deleted or when saveDeletion is true.

        java.io.IOException - if file url is badly formatted.
